Q1 (05/29/2020): Dear Sir, Since this is an STTR topic, can you let me know if you have already identified the University or Government lab â and the corresponding contact (you have mentioned Sandia and North Carolina State University) from which you expect the technology transfer to take place?   - Thanks. Dr. Srinivasan Venkatraman
A: <span style="font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;color:#1F497D;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA">The NCSU and Sandia simulation capabilities were identified as potential starting points to achieve the very ambitious goals of this topic. They are both publically available at the links noted in the references to the topic. I do not have individual contacts, although you can probably find them from the references or the related web sites. Their use is not required. The proposing company is responsible to identify the best approach to achieving the topic goals. Selection of the STTR university partner is the responsibility of the proposing company. The proposing company is expected to develop the transition / commercialization plan and this is one of the evaluation </span> <span style="font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;
