minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:
EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA">The government will provide physical samples or requirements and the contractor will perform measurements. The government will conduct independent measurements but would like the contractor to perform their own measurements for the purpose of demonstrating the utility of the developed tools / models.</span>

Q2 (06/10/2020): For Phase 1, it is understood that the government possesses concrete samples for which remote sensing data can be made available to performers. Could you provide further information in this regard? How is such data to be distributed, and in what format? What are the physical properties of the samples? What are the characteristics of the apparatus used for performing the measurements?
A: <span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;
