minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:
EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA">-ERDC has a variety of concrete reference materials available for analysis to be performed. We anticipate providing data on at least one of these well characterized materials to the contractor during Phase 1. Another option which is preferable would be the provision of a physical sample for the contractor to perform their own measurements. We envision that during Phase 1 the contractor will demonstrate their approach as a proof of concept for prediction of response to a subset of the remote sensing modalities described in the solicitation. For example, for the reference material used, predict the bulk response to a commonly available hyperspectral or multi-spectral sensor. This data is available to provide to the contractor but as mentioned we would prefer for the contract to independently conduct their own measurements. We envision that the details of this would be discussed with the contractor in communications in conjunction with the contracting process to support a timely execution of Phase 1 once contracts are awarded.</span>

<p class="MsoPlainText">- Small datasets may be distributed via email such as spectra. We will make larger datasets such as images, 3D model files, etc available through DODSAFE file transfers or electronically accessible sharepoint sites.

<p class="MsoPlainText">- Physical samples consist of concrete and other geomaterials available in small to large sizes. For example, for the reference concrete materials, we have sizes available of 6&quot; cubes, 12&quot;x12&quot;x3&quot; panels, and 36&quot;x36&quot;x3&quot; panels. Supporting information on constituent materials and proportions will also be made available to the contractor. 3D representations of the internal microstructure and phase distribution is also available for these materials in a 3D solid or meshed finite element format.

