EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA">- If this is referring to remote sensing measurements, some specific parameters are sensitive. The general sensing modalities considered include SWIR, MWIR, LWIR, full hyperspectral and multi-spectral sensors / cameras, polarimetric imaging at a range of geometric configurations between source and sensor and degress of polarization of 90 and +/- 45, as well as various bands / frequencies of synthetic aperture radar. Again, during Phase 1, the contractor is anticipated to provide a proof of concept on a subset of these remote sensing modalities. Additional work during Phase 2 would expand scope to a broader range of materials and remote sensing modalities. </span>
